  ⚠ Important Considerations

  1. Security - Clean Up First

  Before pushing to GitHub, audit for secrets:
  # Check for hardcoded credentials
  grep -r "password\|api_key\|secret" --include="*.py" core/ adapters/

  # Verify .env is gitignored
  cat .gitignore  # Should include .env, .env.local, credentials/

  SKUEL uses these secrets (from CLAUDE.md):
  - NEO4J_URI, NEO4J_USER, NEO4J_PASSWORD
  - OPENAI_API_KEY
  - DEEPGRAM_API_KEY

  Ensure these are never committed - always loaded from environment.

  2. .gitignore Essentials

  # Secrets
  .env
  .env.local
  .env.production
  credentials/
  *.key
  *.pem

  # Data
  /data/
  /neo4j-import/
  *.db
  *.sqlite

  # Python
  __pycache__/
  *.pyc
  .pytest_cache/
  .mypy_cache/
  .ruff_cache/
  htmlcov/

  # IDE
  .vscode/
  .idea/
  *.swp

  # OS
  .DS_Store
  Thumbs.db

  3. Public vs Private

  Start Private:
  - Free for unlimited private repos (GitHub)
  - Keep control while you develop
  - Can open source later if desired

  Go Public Later If:
  - You want to showcase the architecture
  - Open to community contributions
  - Educational value (your patterns are excellent!)

