  📋 Recommended Setup Process

  Phase 1: Initialize Git Locally

  cd /home/mike/skuel0

  # Initialize git
  git init

  # Create .gitignore (see above)
  nano .gitignore

  # Initial commit
  git add .
  git commit -m "Initial commit: SKUEL knowledge graph platform

  - 102k+ lines of service code
  - Protocol-based architecture
  - Result[T] error handling
  - Three-tier type system
  - 100+ test cases"

  Phase 2: Create GitHub Repo

  1. Go to github.com/new
  2. Name: skuel (or skuel-knowledge-graph)
  3. Private initially
  4. Don't initialize with README (you have one)
  5. Push local repo:

  git remote add origin git@github.com:yourusername/skuel.git
  git branch -M main
  git push -u origin main

  Phase 3: Set Up GitHub Actions

  # .github/workflows/quality.yml
  name: Code Quality

  on: [push, pull_request]

  jobs:
    quality:
      runs-on: ubuntu-latest
      steps:
        - uses: actions/checkout@v3

        - uses: actions/setup-python@v4
          with:
            python-version: '3.12'

        - name: Install Poetry
          run: curl -sSL https://install.python-poetry.org | python3 -

        - name: Install Dependencies
          run: poetry install

        - name: Format Check
          run: poetry run ruff format --check

        - name: Lint
          run: poetry run ruff check

        - name: Type Check
          run: poetry run mypy core/

        - name: Run Tests
          run: poetry run pytest tests/ -v

  Phase 4: Documentation Hosting (Optional)

  # .github/workflows/docs.yml
  # Publish /docs to GitHub Pages

